## What is the purpose of the change
i set up a ThreadPoolExecutor to run a task which cantains some dubbo invoke, but i can`t cancel the task, because dubbo will treat it as a normal exception(like timeout exception) and will try again. so i think interrupt exception should be throw out
```
Future<?> future =RUNNER_EXECUTOR.submit(() -> {
    pipelineService.startTask(taskId);
});
TimeUnit.SECONDS.sleep(2);
//cancel task
future.cancel();
